article.headline: Northern Arizona 88, Idaho State 80
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Kelly Golob scored 29 points and Ruben Boykin Jr. added 17 as Northern Arizona held on to beat Idaho State 88-80 Thursday night. Steven Sir finished with 14 points and Tyrone Bazy had 10 for the Lumberjacks (17-7, 9-1 Big Sky). Idaho State (10-12, 2-8) was paced by Tim Henry's 18 points. David Schroeder had 17 points and Slim Millien 16 for the Bengals. Northern Arizona led 43-38 at halftime and was up by 16 points in the second half before Idaho State used a 10-1 run to close to 81-79 with one minure remaining. But the Lumberjacks, who were 32 of 36 from the line, made all six of their free throws down the stretch to seal the win. Golob had 29 of his points in the first half. He finished with eight field goals in 12 attempts, including two 3-pointers, and sank 11 of 12 free throws.
